Through my weekly commitment to students at Bosco Jomo, I have learned the value of giving time to others and become a student-advocate. Even though I go only once a week for an hour and a half, they share the challenges of living away from their parents. Seeing the lack of interactive learning materials inspires me to study ICT so I can create accessible learning tools and offline-compatible programs for students without resources. To make learning fun and improve my leadership, I create games and read long essays with them. After tutoring, we play basketball, and I enjoy organizing zone games where everyone tries different positions, learning patience, teamwork, and adaptability. My spiritual school and community support help me approach all these activities with care, love, and a goal to build scalable educational solutions for underserved youth.
